values: To surrender something is to give it up.
The thief surrendered the money to the police when he was caught.
v. to agree to stop fighting, hiding, resisting, etc., because you know that you will not win or succeed 投降
v. to give the control or use of to someone else 交出
v. to allow something to influence or control you 放任
